---
name: scljet-sql-ipk-rowid
description: SclJet INTEGER PRIMARY KEY aliases the rowid (SQLite semantics); matches reference sqlite3
backends: [int, js]
---

# SclJet INTEGER PRIMARY KEY = rowid alias

A column declared `INTEGER PRIMARY KEY` is an alias for the rowid: on `INSERT`, its value becomes the
rowid (so rows scan in that column's order, not insertion order), a missing/NULL IPK gets the next
auto rowid (max seen + 1), and `SELECT ipk`/`SELECT rowid` return the same value. A duplicate IPK is
rejected (duplicate rowid). Every result matches reference sqlite3 running the same SQL (verified
out-of-band); locked across `[int, js]`. This is the semantics that lets `WHERE ipk = K` become a
rowid point-lookup.

[ByteSlice, SqliteValue, SqlInteger, SqlText, buildTableDatabase](std/scljet/index.ssc)
[queryImage, executeMutation, renderRows](std/scljet/sql.ssc)

```scalascript
def apply(db: ByteSlice, sql: String): ByteSlice =
  executeMutation(db, sql) match
    case Left(m) =>
      println(sql + " => ERR:" + m)
      db
    case Right(next) => next

def show(db: ByteSlice, sql: String): Unit =
  queryImage(db, sql) match
    case Left(m) => println(sql + " => ERR:" + m)
    case Right(rows) => println(sql + " => " + renderRows(rows).toString)

buildTableDatabase(512, 1, 1, "t", "CREATE TABLE t(id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY, name TEXT)",
  List(List(SqlInteger(1L), SqlText("seed")))) match
  case Left(error) => println("build-error:" + error.message)
  case Right(db0) =>
    val db1 = apply(db0, "DELETE FROM t")
    val db2 = apply(db1, "INSERT INTO t VALUES (5,'a'),(2,'b'),(9,'c')")
    show(db2, "SELECT id, name FROM t")
    show(db2, "SELECT rowid, id FROM t")
    val db3 = apply(db2, "INSERT INTO t(name) VALUES ('d')")
    show(db3, "SELECT id, name FROM t")
    val db4 = apply(db3, "INSERT INTO t(name, id) VALUES ('e', 3)")
    show(db4, "SELECT id, name FROM t ORDER BY id")
    show(db4, "SELECT name FROM t WHERE id = 9")
    val dbDup = apply(db4, "INSERT INTO t VALUES (5,'x')")
    show(dbDup, "SELECT id FROM t ORDER BY id")
```
